// Modal form component that users will set their filters. import { useState, useEffect } from 'react'; import ReactModal from 'react-modal'; export default function FilterForm({setFilters, filters}) { function formReset() { document.getElementById("filterForm").reset(); } // modal visibility state and toggle const [isModalOpen, setisModalOpen] = useState(false); const handleChange = (e) => { setFilters({...filters, [e.target.name]: e.target.value}); } const handleCheckboxChange = (e) => { if(e.target.checked) { setFilters({ ...filters, ['power_type']: [...filters.power_type, e.target.value] }); } else { let newData = {...filters}; newData.power_type.filter(type => { return e.target.value != type }); setFilters(newData); } } /* FOR DEBUGGING */ useEffect(() => { console.log(filters); }, [filters]) function openModal() { setisModalOpen(true); document.body.style.overflow = 'hidden'; } function updateAll() { setisModalOpen(false) document.body.style.overflow = 'unset'; // setFilters({ // min_power: {min_power_value}, // max_power: {max_power_value}, // min_power_bonus: {min_power_bonus_value}, // max_power_bonus: 1, // min_attr_bonus: 0, // max_attr_bonus: 1, // min_luck: 0, // max_luck: 500, // min_title_req: 0, // max_title_req: 15, // min_cheese_effect: 0, // max_cheese_effect: 12, // }) } return ( <>
